The key insight: the mutation changes `if (!path.isAbsolute(options.dest))` to `if (true)`. For an already-absolute path like `/tmp/image.jpg`, `path.resolve(__dirname, '/tmp/image.jpg')` still returns `/tmp/image.jpg` - same result. But for a path with `..` segments like `/tmp/../tmp/image.jpg`, `path.resolve` normalizes it to `/tmp/image.jpg`, while the original code leaves it unchanged.

